I've been looking into this. Would it be possible to put an iterator into Sequence that can be filled at a later time?
```python
class Spigot:
    def __init__(self):
        self.iterator = None

    def __call__(self, iterable):
        self.iterator = iter(iterable)
        return self

    def __iter__(self):
        return self

    def __next__(self):
        return next(self.iterator)
```
This iterator gives us access to the beginning of our function pipe. If we want to use the pipe again we can fill it again.
It gets trickier when there gets to functions that don't just pass the values through like max or first because those or kind of dead ends that cannot be requested from with next.

